<title>GERMANY: BHW -H1 97 post-tax profit up 28.7 percent.</title>
<headline>BHW -H1 97 post-tax profit up 28.7 percent.</headline>
<dateline>HAMELN, Germany 1997-07-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>German savings, financing and insurance company BHW AG said on Thursday that first-half 1997 post-tax profit was 126.3 million marks, a rise of 28.7 percent.</p>
<p>Group operating profit in the first half of 1997 was 270 million marks, up 13.5 percent, the recently-floated group said in a compulsory statement.</p>
<p>The group said that stable growth in new business had increased its market share.</p>
<p>BHW was selected on Tuesday for inclusion in the MDAX index of 70 medium-sized German firms in September.</p>
<p>--Frankfurt Newsroom +49 69 756525</p>
